<promed@promedmail.org>
[In fact on 18 Aug 2000 ProMED-mail carried a report of a case of hand,
foot & mouth disease in Hong Kong (see Hand, foot & mouth disease - China (Hong
Kong) 20000818.1374). A 5-year-old girl had died after being infected by a
virus during a trip to the mainland. This was the second fatal case of
Enterovirus type 71 (EV71) infection recorded since the government set up a
surveillance programme during outbreaks in 1998. In May of 2000 a boy 3
years of age was reported to have fully recovered after a mild EV71
infection. The virus responsible for the current outbreak in Hong Kong has
not yet been identified. - Mod.CP
